  "body": "Using https://github.com/mds1/convex-shutdown-simulation as the test repo for the below snippets\r\n\r\nIf you set the gas limit to 15000000 in your `.env` file and run `make benchmark-foundry`, you'll see the below. It'd be nice for the reason to say \"out of gas\". Similarly, this is not clear from the trace if you run with `-vvv`\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ make benchmark-foundry\r\nbash scripts/benchmark-foundry.sh\r\ncompiling...\r\nno files changed, compilation skipped.\r\nRunning 1 test for ConvexTest.json:ConvexTest\r\n[FAIL. Reason: ] testShutdownCost() (gas: 14245509)\r\nError: \r\n   0: Encountered a total of 1 failing tests, 0 tests succeeded\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli/src/cmd/test.rs:187\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n\r\nreal    0m10.778s\r\nuser    0m1.346s\r\nsys     0m0.540s\r\nmake: *** [benchmark-foundry] Error 1\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
